- `ls -al`: List all files in the current directory
- `cat [file.txt]`: Read contents of the file
- `pwd`: Displays your current directory
- `cd [dir_name]`: Change directory
- `mkdir [dir_name]`: Make a new directory
- `whoami`: Displays your username
- `id`: Displays your ID, username, and group information
- `rm [file_name]`: Remove files
- `mv [file_name] [destination_dir]`: Move file from one directory to another
- `cp [source_path] [destination_path]`: Copy files from one directory to another
- `find [dir] -name [pattern]`: Finds all files that match the pattern in the directory
- `chmod 777 [filename]`: Change permissions for users, group, and others where rwx rwx rwx for owner group others
- `chown [username] [filename]`: Change ownership of filename
- `sudo [username]`: Change into that user
- `chgrp [groupname] [filename]`: Change group for that file
- `ps`: List running processes
- `kill <PID>`: Kills the process
- `exec`: Execute the command after the pipe
- `ip addr` / `ifconfig`: Shows IP address
- `ping [address]`: Pings the address
- `netstat`: Displays inbound and outbound rules
- `head [filename/path]`: Show the head of the file
- `tail [filename/path]`: Show the tail of the file
- `grep [pattern]`: Finds matching pattern
- `wc [filename.txt]`: Word count
- `sort -n [filename]`: Sort the files in alphabetical order
- `cut [filename]`: Cuts out specific parts of the file
- `gzip [options] [filename]` / `gunzip [options] [filename]`: Gzip compresses the filename
- `tar [filename.tar] [file]`: Compress or archive files
- `uniq`: Displays unique files/lines in a file
- `printenv`: Print environment variables
- `umask`: Changes permissions for a file
- `du`: Disk utilization
- `df`: Free disk space
- `dirname`: Displays directory name
- `jobs`: Displays all jobs that are running
- `bg` / `fg`: Run a process in the background and foreground
- `type`: Shows what kind it isâ€”executable / shell built-in program / shell function / alias
- `which docker`: Find shell path
- `xargs`: Changes one command output to an argument
- `passwd`: Changes password
- `traceroute [host]`: Displays the route to reach the host
- `locate`: Find a file
- `cat /etc/passwd`: See user details
- `cat /etc/group`: See group details
- `useradd/userdel [username]`: Username add/delete
- `telnet [host]`: Interactive session with host
- `free`: Free space
- `lsb_release -a`: Which Ubuntu version are we using
- `curl [host]`: Connect to a server with HTTP
- `sudo openconnect`: Connect to VPN
- `lscpu`: Show CPU info
- `scp user@machine`: Copy file to machine
- `/etc/shadow`: Password stored in hash
